## Inline Math

The kinetic energy of a moving body is $KE = \frac{1}{2}mv^2$, while its
momentum is simply $p = mv$. For small oscillations, $\sin\theta \approx \theta$.

## Fundamental Equations

@math name="Mass–Energy Equivalence" label="eq:einstein"
E = mc^2
@/math

@math name="Newton's Second Law" label="eq:newton"
F = ma
@/math

As shown in @ref(eq:einstein) and @ref(eq:newton), these two equations
anchor classical and relativistic mechanics respectively.

## The Quadratic Formula

@math name="Quadratic Formula" label="eq:quadratic"
x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
@/math

## Calculus

@math name="Gaussian Integral" label="eq:gaussian"
\int_{0}^{\infty} e^{-x^2}\,dx = \frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}
@/math

@math name="Definition of a Limit"
\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin x}{x} = 1
@/math

@math name="A Convergent Series"
\sum_{i=1}^{n} i = \frac{n(n+1)}{2}
@/math

## Linear Algebra

A 2×2 matrix and its determinant-defining transformation:

@math env=align label="eq:matrix-system"
\begin{pmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix}
&=
\begin{pmatrix} ax + by \\ cx + dy \end{pmatrix}
@/math

## Piecewise Functions

@math name="Absolute Value, Defined Piecewise"
f(x) = \begin{cases}
  x & x \geq 0 \\
  -x & x < 0
\end{cases}
@/math

## Vectors & Set Theory

Force as a vector quantity: $\vec{F} = m\vec{a}$, where mass $m \in \mathbb{R}^+$.

For any two sets, $A \cup B$ and $A \cap B$ satisfy $|A \cup B| = |A| + |B| - |A \cap B|$.

## Multi-Step Derivation

@math env=align label="eq:power-derivation"
F &= ma \\
W &= F \cdot d \\
P &= \frac{W}{t}
@/math

The full derivation in @ref(eq:power-derivation) connects force, work, and power.

